Kansas proposal will block transgender people from updating their birth certificates

article_metadata.news-keywords: Kansas, 2016, Legislature, taxes, tax cuts, Brownback, governor, Wagle, Supreme Court, school finance, business tax cut
article_metadata.description: The 2016 legislative session has seen a bill to make it easier to impeach Supreme Court justices, an attempt to override Gov. Sam Brownback’s vetoes and the ouster of committee chairs after they bucked legislative leaders. Every session has a fair amount of conflict, but this one has seen an unusual amount of intraparty wrangling.
